Use the principle of mathematical induction to prove that1⋅21+2⋅22+3⋅23+⋯+n⋅2n=2+(n−1)2n+1for alln∈Z+.\begin{aligned}
\hspace{4em} 1\cdot2^1 + 2\cdot2^2 + 3\cdot2^3 + \cdots + n\cdot2^n &= 2 + (n-1)2^{n+1} \hspace{2em} \text{for all } n \in \mathbb{Z}^+. \\
\end{aligned}1⋅21+2⋅22+3⋅23+⋯+n⋅2n​=2+(n−1)2n+1for alln∈Z+.​

