    3n^3-7n^2+5 &= 0 \\[10pt]
    3n^3+5 &= 7n^2 \\[-12pt]
\end{align*}3n3−7n2+53n3+5​=0=7n2​Consider first the case wherennnis odd.3n33n^33n3is odd and hence3n3+53n^3 + 53n3+5is even.7n27n^27n2is odd, therefore3n3+5≠7n2\begin{align*}
    3n^3+5 &\neq 7n^2 \\[-12pt]
\end{align*}3n3+5​=7n2​Now consider the case wherennnis even.3n33n^33n3is even and hence3n3+53n^3 + 53n3+5is odd.7n27n^27n2is even, therefore3n3+5≠7n2\begin{align*}
    3n^3+5 &\neq 7n^2 \\[-12pt]
\end{align*}3n3+5​=7n2​We have shown that forn∈Zn \in \mathbb{Z}n∈Z, whethernnnis odd or even, the equation is not satisfied. Hence there is a contradiction.Thus our original assumption is false, and by the method of proof by contradiction, we conclude that3x3−7x2+5=03x^3-7x^2+5=03x3−7x2+5=0has no integer roots.

